OL,3,CHospitality bosses warn NICs changes
OL,4,C'regressive in impact' on lower earners
OL,6,FThe main tax rise in Ms Reeves' fiscal
OL,7,Fstatement was a change to employers'
OL,8,FNational Insurance contributions which
OL,9,Fis expected to raise more than
OL,10,F#25billion for the Treasury.
OL,12,FAs well as an increase in the rate
OL,13,Femployers pay, from 13.8% to 15%, the
OL,14,Fthreshold at which employers start
OL,15,Fpaying the tax will be reduced from
OL,16,F#9,100 per year to #5,000.
OL,18,FAccording to the Times, hospitality
OL,19,Fbosses are calling for a lower NICs
OL,20,Frate of 5% for those earning between
OL,21,F#5,000 and #9,100, or an exemption.
